50|$|The {{incidents}} of enforced disappearances were condemned by {{both domestic and}} international human rights organizations. The main opposition party BNP has held the government responsible for conducting these <b>forced</b> <b>disappearances,</b> and demanded an UN-sponsored investigation into such cases. The British parliament frequently expressed concerns over the <b>forced</b> <b>disappearances</b> of political opponents in Bangladesh. During her visit to Bangladesh in 2012, former U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton expressed concern over the disappearance of Ilyas Ali and Aminul Islam. Despite the demands for the government initiatives to probe such disappearances, investigations into such cases were absent.|$|R
